  "heading": "\\partially.ordered{X}",
  "heading_latex": "\\textrm{partially ordered}",
  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\partially.ordered{X}]\nStates:\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nthat:\n. allOf:\n  . forAll: a is \\set\n    where:\n    . a \"in\" X\n    then:\n    . a \\:precedes:/ a\n  . forAll: a, b is \\set\n    where:\n    . a \"in\" X\n    . b \"in\" X\n    then:\n    . if:\n      . allOf:\n        . a \\:precedes:/ b\n        . b \\:precedes:/ a\n      then:\n      . a = b\n  . forAll: a, b, c is \\set\n    where:\n    . a \"in\" X\n    . b \"in\" X\n    . c \"in\" X\n    then:\n    . if:\n      . allOf:\n        . a \\:precedes:/ b\n        . b \\:precedes:/ c\n      then:\n      . a \\:precedes:/ c\nDocumented:\n. called: \"partially ordered\"\n. written: \"X? \\text{ is partially ordered}\"\n. description: \"A set $X$ is partially ordered by $\\preceq$ when $\\preceq$ is reflexive, asymmetric, and transitive on $X$. Some pairs of elements may be incomparable.\"\nId: \"dc09bd71-fafe-42e4-a2cb-abefe68a04fd\"",
